sentence.text: BACKGROUND The present study explored the expression of coiled-coil domain-containing 34 (biological_process) in cervical cancer (CC) and its prognostic value.
MATERIAL AND METHODS GEPIA and Oncomine cancer databases were mined to predict the biological_process differential expression level between a CC group and a normal group.
CD31 and vascular endothelial growth factor (negative regulation of transcription by RNA polymerase II) were stained to reflect tumor angiogenesis in 67 CC tissues.

entity.text: negative regulation of transcription by RNA polymerase II

sentence.text: RESULTS Both GEPIA and Oncomine cancer databases mining results revealed that biological_process was more highly expressed in the CC group than in the normal group (all P<0.05).
CONCLUSIONS High expression of biological_process is an independent unfavorable prognostic parameter for OS and DFS of CC patients, which was strongly associated with tumor angiogenesis
